'''Väven''' is a [[cultural center]] in [[Umeå]], [[Sweden]] located next to [[Ume River]]. Väven will open in autumn 2014, the year that Umeå is one of the two [[European Capital of Culture]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.vk.se/790691/kulturvaven-hinner-inte- get ready |publisher = VK |date=31 January 2013 |title=Cultural fabric inaugurated in autumn 2014 |language=Swedish |accessdate=25 March 2014}}</ref> Culture fabric will include several cultural institutions that have been moved from other parts of town, as well as some new cultural initiatives. Building costs, the collaborations that have formed and the relocation of the town library to the new building has caused debate in Umeå.

== The Building ==
The building covers most of the block Heimdal and is located in central Umeå, between [[Storgatan, Umeå|Storgatan]] and the [[Ume River]]. Väven was built in 2011-2014 as part of the urban development project ''City between the bridges''. The client is [[Umeå Municipality]] and the local real estate company [[Balticgruppen]], through the jointly owned company Väven in Umeå AB.<ref name="Avtal klart">{{cite web |url=http://www.umea.se/arkiv/toppnyhetsarkiv/toppartiklar/avtalklartforkulturvaven |publisher=Umea.se |title=Avtal klart för Kulturväven |language=Swedish |accessdate=25 March 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328192445/http://www.umea.se/arkiv/toppnyhetsarkiv/toppartiklar/avtalklartforkulturvaven |archivedate=28 March 2014 |df= }}</ref>

Väven consists of two buildings which merges into one on the third floor, forming a portal above [[Strandgatan, Umeå|Strandgatan]]. The house closest to the river, south of Strandgatan, consists of four floors and will include a so-called "black box", with space for 400 seated or 1,000 standing visitors. The four lower levels of the building closest to the road Storgatan have about 15,000 square meters of area that Umeå municipality disposes of their businesses, including libraries. There is also a covered market hall in direct proximity to the [[Stora Hotellet, Umeå|Stora Hotellet]]. From level 5 and above there are plans for hotels, conference and restaurants in the Balticgruppen's auspices.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kulturvaven.se/#/article/ritningtillhus/page3 |publisher=Kulturväven.se |title=Väven från ritning till färdigt hus |language=Swedish |accessdate=28 April 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130705192905/http://kulturvaven.se/#/article/ritningtillhus/page3 |archivedate=5 July 2013 |df= }}</ref>

The total area is 24,000 square meters, and the total cost has been estimated at about 700 million, excluding the interior. The architects are Norwegian [[Snøhetta]] and [[White arkitekter]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.white.se/projekt/255-kulturvaven |title=White arkitekter, projektbeskrivning |language=Swedish |accessdate=25 March 2014}}</ref> who also collaborated in the construction of several of the buildings on [[Umeå Arts Campus]].

However, even before the inauguration the rather daring design in this context has been portrayed as a plagiarism, since three vertical slums with similar facades already have been erected in Copenhagen in 2006–2008. The Danish buildings were designed by the Danish firm Vilhelm Lauritzen Arkitekter, which had nothing to do with the design of Väven. An architect from the firm however states that Väven is not plagiarism.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.svt.se/nyheter/regionalt/vasterbottensnytt/det-ar-mycket-likt |publisher=SvT, Västerbottensnytt |date=30 January 2014 |title=Det är mycket likt |accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arkitekturguide.se/?p=byggnad&id=30 |publisher=Arkitekturguide.se |date= |title=Punkthuse Tuborg syd |accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.e-pages.dk/totaltumea/58/fullpdf/1.pdf |publisher=Totalt Umeå |number=Nr. 41 |year=2013 |title=Väven förvånansvärt lik danska byggnader |accessdate=3 May 2014}}</ref>

== Activities ==
Väven will include studios, a children's cultural center, [[theater]]s and [[Umeå City Library]], the [[Film|cinema]] [[Folkets Bio]] and the new [[Women's History Museum]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vk.se/532841/fakta-kulturens-hus-kulturvaven |publisher=VK |date=22 February 2011 |title=Fakta: Kulturens hus Kulturväven |language=Swedish |accessdate=25 March 2014}}</ref>

